texts.text: >One day at the Hideout...
Yoohoo! How's it going everyone? It's your favorite person Seiran who you haven't seen in a while!
Sorry for the short notice, by the way.

Well, it's okay but...
Some members couldn't make it.
I did call for this meeting at the very last moment, so it can't be helped.
I think we'll do just fine with this many of you here. Thank you for coming.
So, what's this about?
Let me guess, you sensed another Dragon Stream anomaly?
Oh, you read my mind.
I don't need to because lately that's all you come here for.
Wait a minute, you mean you think I'm like some kind of Dragon Stream alarm?
N-No! Of course not! Right, miss Koden?
Just a little.
Miss Koden!
Hahaha, she got you there, miss gatekeeper.
I guess there's no denying it...
Being gatekeeper to the Aura Gate keeps me busy at all times.
I don't have the time to come hang out because I take my job very seriously.
Feel free to come and hang out with me at the Aura Gate though?
I don't think that's the kind of place people go to hang out...
Aight, so what's with this Dragon Stream anomaly?
Oh yeah, right.
So I've already went on location to investigate and...
Hmm, how should I put this...
Remember the time when a bunch of abandoned buildings got eroded by the spiritual world?
How could I forget a thing like that?
Yes, that was the incident where the spiritual world created by the Asuras got so big that
it started merging with our reality,
creating an Aura Gate of sorts.
That's right. And the anomaly I found this time
is basically the same phenomenon.
So it's another world intruding upon ours like last time?
No, it hasn't gotten to that point yet.
And the location is in the Aura Gate itself.
It's like somebody added this space inside when I wasn't looking.
What the hell...
It's kind of structured like a maze,
so I thought better off going in alone and came back.
Then I called Megakin and now here we are...
So what we know for now is...
an unknown spiritual space has appeared in the Aura Gate,
and it's disrupting the flow of the Dragon Stream.
Is that all?
Yes. But it's not serious enough to cause a disaster or anything.
I just did a brief search. No strange cases or disappearances going on lately as far as I can tell.
Not yet.
So you want us to investigate it because you're not sure what would happen if we ignored it?
That's right. All I need for now is a brief recon mission.
We should be able to manage that with just the members that are here right now.
Aight, take us to this place then.
We're here! This is the place.
It really does look like just another part of the Aura Gate.
Does this really need any investigating?
Of course. If it turns out to be a false alarm, that's for the best..
But even though it looks just like any other part of the Aura Gate, we don't know what's in there.
This is the Aura Gate we're talking about, anything is possible.
Sometimes the insides of these floors can be literally worlds apart..
Seiran's right. We should treat it as the unknown, no matter what it looks like.
Anyways, we should start by looking around a bit first.
Looking around a bit? Is that safe?
Yeah, I think. It's not like we're going to find anything standing here anyways...
And I think I sense some energy coming from over that way.
Aight, since that's our only lead right now, we should go.
Yes, we're definitely getting close. This way.
...Wait up y'all! You guys hear somethin' down that way?
>At Megakin's words, everyone starts to advance more cautiously with their ears raised.
>There seems to be a fight going on...
Ya!
Aaargh...

Phew! That was a very tough evil spirit...
Thank you Lord for protecting me.
Is that... A demon?
It just placed its head on the ground and started praying...
Hey, doesn't the demon that got killed seem odd?
It's not dissipating like normal...
>As the demon dissipates, something that looks like energy emerges from it...
>It floats for a while, then it disappears after coming into contact with the praying demon.
It was absorbed?
...Who's there?
Wo! Chill man. We ain't here to fight.
...I can tell.
You're the first ones I've encountered here who did not attack me on sight.
You must forgive me for my harsh manner just now. I am Tokisada
I'm Megakin.
So I'm just gonna ask you straight up. You know this place?
I'm sorry to say that I don't.
I was already here when I came to, and realized I have taken on an inhuman form.
What?
The entities that assaulted me were also demonic in form.
Could this be Paradise? No, that's impossible.
Excuse me, but you said you took on an inhuman form...
Tokisada. I call to you Tokisada. The poor child of man who was graced with God's love.
Who's there?!
>You look around but could not find the origin of the voice.
>It is as if the voice came from the heavens.
What is going on?
Listen carefully, Tokisada.
It was God's will that you be resurrected here in this place.
Yes, you died. And it was God who took you from the brink of death and gave you new life.
Is that true?! God revived me?
Yes, for you have fought for Him. You have proven your love and devotion to God.
So your prayers were answered,
and you have been resurrected here by His mercy.
But... But why me? I am powerless... Without worth...
There is no need to worry. Surely you have felt your power grow
as you slayed the Godless evil that confronted you.
This ability is God's blessing, given only to the chosen.
It is proof that you were resurrected by the hand of God.
O thank the Lord and His messenger who speaks from the heavens.
Now go forth and destroy the evil beings that infest this land.
Take their power as your own so you could slay even greater evil.
This is God's will. The Lord has great expectations for you.
Yes. I, Tokisada, shall bear up arms once more so God's mercy on me would not be in vain.
May the Lord's blessing be with you.
>The voice from the heavens ceases to speak.
And there you have it. I must take my leave now.
Do you really believe what that voice told you?
How do you know who you're talking to when you can't even see them?

...?
Isn't that what Faith in God is all about?
Even if you can't see Him, He is there. The Creator of life who watches over us all.
And who else but God can perform such a miracle as resurrecting the dead?
To doubt the Lord's mercy is blasphemy. I will not do so.
Now I shall bid you farewell. May we meet again some time.
>Tokisada leaves.
There he goes.
Well Seiran, what do we do? Do we continue to investigate or what?
Hmmm, I'll need more info before I can say for sure
if this place is going to cause trouble or not.
Let's continue investigating a bit longer.
